===================================================
   Redberry - Symbolic Tensor Algebra. Pure Java
===================================================

 Redberry  is an open source Java framework providing
 core functionality of computer algebra system focused
 on working with objects with indices (tensors).

 For information about latests releases, downloads and 
 example code please visit our site:
 
   homepage:   http://cc.redberry.bitbucket.org/
   bitbucket:   https://bitbucket.org/cc.redberry/cc.redberry
   

 This program is a free software: you can redistribute it and/or
 modify it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as
 published by the Free Software Foundation, either version 2 of the
 License, or (at your option) any later version. Full license text 
 you can find in COPYING file.



 Requirements
----------------------------------------

 JDK 7 or later (http://jdk7.java.net/download.html)
 
 To build cc.redberry from source Maven 2.2 or later required (http://maven.apache.org/).
 
 Working with Redberry source code or repository requires both 
 Maven and Mercurial 1.9.0 or later (http://mercurial.selenic.com/)

 
 Working with jar
---------------------------------

 Download  cc.redberry-x.x.x-jar-with-dependencies.jar.tar.gz file
 (x.x.x - current version) from Redberry site or bitbucket 
 page and unpack it. Create your java project and add 
 cc.redberry-x.x.x-jar-with-dependencies.jar file to your  project
 dependencies as jar library. Now you can work with Redberry API
 in your project.


 Working with maven
---------------------------------------

 Public maven repository coming soon!!!

 To include cc.redberry now follow instructions below:
 
 Download  cc.redberry-x.x.x.jar.tar.gz file  (x.x.x - current version
 indices) from Redberry site or bitbucket page and unpack it.
 Now add cc.redberry-x.x.x.jar file to your maven repositorie by
 typing in command line:
 
           mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=cc.redberry
           -DartifactId=cc.redberry -Dversion=x.x.x
           -Dfile=cc.redberry-x.x.x.jar -Dpackaging=jar -DgeneratePom=true

 Add following lines in dependencies section in your pom.xml file:

         <dependency>
            <groupId>cc.redberry</groupId>
            <artifactId>cc.redberry</artifactId>
            <version>0.8.0</version>
            <scope>compile</scope>
         </dependency>
         <dependency>
            <groupId>ch.qos.logback</groupId>
            <artifactId>logback-classic</artifactId>
            <version>0.9.29</version>
         </dependency>


Working with source code
-------------------------------------------
 To work with Redberry source code use Mercurial 1.9.0 or later
 (http://mercurial.selenic.com/). To clone cc.redberry repository
 type in command line:
 
     hg clone https://bitbucket.org/cc.redberry/cc.redberry
	 
 Or you can download a package with source code from our bitbucket
 page.
 
 To build cc.redberry from source Maven 2.2 or later required (http://maven.apache.org/).
 Use this command to build cc.redberry with all dependencies:
 
     mvn assembly:single
 
 Or this:
 
     mvn jar:jar
	 
 to build jar with cc.redberry only.
 
Working with Redberry repositorie
-------------------------------------------------------
 If you want to contribute and develop Redberry, first sing up bitbucket
 and pass to Redberry page. There you will find fork link - click it and 
 follow instructions. If you will develop some feature fill free to 
 contact authors and pull your module in main repositories.
 
 
